X(3872): propagating in a dense medium

Abstract

In cold nuclear matter, the shifts in the mass and current-meson coupling as well the vector self energy of the exotic X‚Äã(3872)ùëã3872X(3872) are calculated using the diquark-antidiquark current within the framework of the in-medium two-point QCD sum rule. At the rest frame of the medium, the three momentum of the considered particle is fixed to remove the contributions of the particles with negative energy. In the calculations, we include the in-medium condensates of quark-quark, gluon-gluon and quark-gluon. It is observed that, the shift due to the nuclear matter is negative and is about 25%percent2525\% when the saturation density is used. Such shift is considerably large and comparable with the nucleon‚Äô mass shift due to the nuclear medium. The negative shift in the current-meson coupling due to nuclear matter is approximately 10%percent1010\%. At the saturation density, the vector self energy of the exotic X‚Äã(3872)ùëã3872X(3872) state is found to be Œ£œÖ=1.31subscriptŒ£ùúê1.31\Sigma_{\upsilon}=1.31 GeV. It is shown that the mass, current-meson coupling and vector self energy of X‚Äã(3872)ùëã3872X(3872) strongly depend on the density of cold nuclear matter.

I Introduction

In recent years, the new hadronic states such as meson-meson, meson-baryon and baryon-baryon molecules, tetraquarks, pentaquarks, hybrids and glueballs have been in the focus of much attention. These exotic states can not be considered as the usual quark-antiquark or three-quark form of the well-known hadronic spectroscopy. Both the quark model and QCD do not exclude the existence of such states. Hence, the investigation of such states can play essential role in understanding of their structures and gaining useful knowledge on the perturbative and non-perturbative natures of QCD.

Among the exotic states, the tetraquark state X‚Äã(3872)ùëã3872X(3872) is one of the most interesting particles. Firstly, the Belle Collaboration Choi:2003ue detected X‚Äã(3872)ùëã3872X(3872) as a narrow charmonium-like state produced in the exclusive decay process B¬±‚ÜíK¬±‚ÄãœÄ+‚ÄãœÄ‚àí‚ÄãJ/œà‚Üísuperscriptùêµplus-or-minussuperscriptùêæplus-or-minussuperscriptùúãsuperscriptùúãùêΩùúìB^{\pm}\rightarrow K^{\pm}\pi^{+}\pi^{-}J/\psi, which decays into œÄ+‚ÄãœÄ‚àí‚ÄãJ/œàsuperscriptùúãsuperscriptùúãùêΩùúì\pi^{+}\pi^{-}J/\psi, with a mass of mX=3872.0¬±0.6subscriptùëöùëãplus-or-minus3872.00.6m_{X}=3872.0\pm 0.6(stat) ¬±0.5plus-or-minus0.5\pm 0.5(syst) MeV. It was confirmed later in some other experiments: CDF II Collaboration Acosta:2003zx via p¬Ø‚Äãp¬Øùëùùëù\bar{p}p collisions with mX=3871.3¬±0.7subscriptùëöùëãplus-or-minus3871.30.7m_{X}=3871.3\pm 0.7(stat) ¬±0.4plus-or-minus0.4\pm 0.4(syst) MeV, D0 Collaboration Abazov:2004kp again in p¬Ø‚Äãp¬Øùëùùëù\bar{p}p collisions with the mass difference between the X‚Äã(3872)ùëã3872X(3872) state and J/œàùêΩùúìJ/\psi as 774.9¬±3.1plus-or-minus774.93.1774.9\pm 3.1 (stat)¬±3.0plus-or-minus3.0\pm 3.0 (syst) MeV and BABAR detector Aubert:2004ns at the PEP-II e+‚Äãe‚àísuperscriptùëísuperscriptùëíe^{+}e^{-} asymmetric-energy storage ring with the mass 3873.4¬±1.4plus-or-minus3873.41.43873.4\pm 1.4 MeV. Belle Collaboration also assigned the quantum numbers of X‚Äã(3872)ùëã3872X(3872) as JP‚ÄãC=1++superscriptùêΩùëÉùê∂superscript1absentJ^{PC}=1^{++} Abe:2005iya . The decay width of X‚Äã(3872)ùëã3872X(3872) state was estimated as ŒìX‚Äã(3872)<1.2subscriptŒìùëã38721.2\Gamma_{X(3872)}<1.2 MeV Nielsen:2009uh ; Choi:2011fc .

Following the discovery of X‚Äã(3872)ùëã3872X(3872) both the theoretical and experimental researches on the non-conventional particles gained an acceleration. Such that, many tetraquark and pentaquark states have been discovered in the experiments and a rush of theoretical papers on the structures of the discovered and possible exotic particles appeared. Despite a lot of theoretical and experimental studies; the structure, nature and quark organisation of the newly founded states have not been understood exactly, yet. There are a lot of suggestions on the nature of the exotic X‚Äã(3872)ùëã3872X(3872) states, for instance, see Refs. Ortega:2017hpw ; Yu:2017bsj ; Zhou:2017dwj ; Wang:2015rcz ; Ferretti:2015fba ; Pena:2014pea ; Guo:2014hqa ; Wang:2013vex ; Baru:2013rta ; Wang:2013kva ; Cui:2011be ; Takizawa:2012hy ; Coito:2012vf ; Chen:2013pya ; Ferretti:2014xqa ; Karliner:2014lta ; Meng:2014ota ; Achasov:2015oia ; Larionov:2015nea ; Larionov:2015kxn ; Maiani:2004vq ; Bugg:2004rk ; Li:2004sta ; Seth:2004zb ; Swanson:2003tb ; Wang:2013daa ; Braaten:2013poa ; Chen:2016qju ; Matheus:2006xi ; Kang:2016jxw ; Sundu:2016oda . In Ref. Maiani:2004vq , for example, it is assumed as a diquark-antidiquark states with hidden or open charm of the forms: [c‚Äãq]‚Äã[c¬Ø‚Äãq¬Ø‚Ä≤]delimited-[]ùëêùëûdelimited-[]¬Øùëêsuperscript¬Øùëû‚Ä≤[cq][\bar{c}\bar{q}^{\prime}] and [c‚Äãq]‚Äã[s¬Ø‚Äãq¬Ø‚Ä≤]delimited-[]ùëêùëûdelimited-[]¬Øùë†superscript¬Øùëû‚Ä≤[cq][\bar{s}\bar{q}^{\prime}] with q,q‚Ä≤=u,dformulae-sequenceùëûsuperscriptùëû‚Ä≤ùë¢ùëëq,q^{\prime}=u,d. In Ref. Bugg:2004rk , it was suggested that it might be a JP‚ÄãC=1++superscriptùêΩùëÉùê∂superscript1absentJ^{PC}=1^{++} cusp due to the D‚ÄãD¬Ø‚àóùê∑superscript¬Øùê∑D\bar{D}^{*} threshold. The author in Ref. Li:2004sta presented a study on the possibility of X‚Äã(3872)ùëã3872X(3872) to be considered as a hybrid state of c‚Äãc¬Ø‚Äãgùëê¬Øùëêùëîc\bar{c}g. In another study, Ref. Seth:2004zb , it is proposed that X‚Äã(3872)ùëã3872X(3872) can be a vector glueball mixed with neighbouring vector states of charmonium. Despite a lot of studies on the structure of X‚Äã(3872)ùëã3872X(3872), it‚Äô nature remains unclear and needs to be investigated further.

Almost all studies on the properties of X‚Äã(3872)ùëã3872X(3872) and other exotic states have been performed in vacuum and there is almost no study on the in-medium properties of non-conventional particles, except Ref. Veliev:2017fpa which investigates the thermal properties of X‚Äã(3872)ùëã3872X(3872). Investigation of the in-medium properties of exotic states, besides the standard hadrons, can play crusial role in the analysing of the results of the heavy-ion collision experiments. Many experimental collaborations, such as PANDA, CBM at FAIR and NICA are planning to study the in-medium properties of hadrons including the newly discovered non-conventional states Prencipe:2015cgg ; Biswas:2015paa ; fair ; panda ; Friman ; Lutz:2009ff ; Giacosa:2015nwa ; nika . For instance, PANDA have focused on the search of the not-yet discovered glueballs and on the already discovered but not-yet understood X,Y,ZùëãùëåùëçX,Y,Z states, Giacosa:2015nwa . Therefore investigation of exotic particles in medium becomes an attractive and exciting subject.

In the present study, we are going to evaluate the spectroscopic parameters such as the mass, current-meson coupling constant and vector self energy of the exotic X‚Äã(3872)ùëã3872X(3872) at cold nuclear medium within the in-medium two-point QCD sum rule method and considering a diquark-antidiquark picture for this particle. We will look for the shifts on the quantities under consideration due to the nuclear matter at a saturation density. We will discuss the variations of parameters of X‚Äã(3872)ùëã3872X(3872) with respect to the variations of the density, as well.

This work is organised in the following way. In section II, the in-medium QCD sum rules for the mass and current-meson coupling of the exotic X‚Äã(3872)ùëã3872X(3872) (in what follows denoted as XùëãX) are obtained. In section III, the numerical analysis of the obtained in-medium sum rules are performed. We investigate the variations of the quantities with respect to the variations of the density and calculate the shifts on the quantities under consideration due to the nuclear matter in this section. The last section includes our concluding remarks.

III Numerical Analyses

For the numerical analyses of the physical quantities under consideration in nuclear matter and vacuum, we need the value of the saturated nuclear matter density and the in-medium and vacuum operators, whose numerical values are presented in Table 1.

Besides these input parameters, the obtained QCD sum rules are also functions of two auxiliary parameters: the Borel mass parameter M2superscriptùëÄ2M^{2} and the continuum threshold s0‚àósubscriptsuperscriptùë†0s^{*}_{0}. The working intervals for these auxiliary parameters are found based on the standard prescriptions of the method used. The standard criteria for the calculation of working intervals for these parameters are weak dependence of the results on these parameters, achieving to the maximum pole contributions (PC), convergence of the series of the OPE and exceeding of the perturbative parts over the non-perturbative contributions. As a result, we get

for M2superscriptùëÄ2M^{2} and

The shift in the meson-current coupling is about %10\%10 and is negative. Such shifts in the mass and residue of XùëãX are comparable with those of the nucleon obtained in Ref. Azizi:2014yea . These considerable shifts in the values of the parameters of XùëãX can be attributed to its up/down quark content which strongly interacts with the nucleons in the medium. IV Conclusion

In this study, we used the interpolating current in a diquark-antidiquark form to investigate the spectroscopic parameters of the famous X‚Äã(3872)ùëã3872X(3872) tetraquark in the cold nuclear matter. This is the first attempt to calculate the properties of non-conventional particles in nuclear matter. The properties of standard hadrons in nuclear medium were previously investigated extensively in the literature (see for instance Refs. Azizi:2016dmr ; Hosaka:2016ypm ; Wang:2012xk ; Wang:2011yj ; Wang:2011hta ; Cohen:1994wm ; Furnstahl:1995nd ; Drukarev:2004fn ; Drukarev:2001wd ; Koike:1996ga ; Hayashigaki:2000es ; Ohtani:2016pyk ; Suzuki:2015est and references theirin). We derived the in-medium sum rules to evaluate the shifts in the mass and current-meson coupling of the X‚Äã(3872)ùëã3872X(3872) as well as found its vector self energy. The obtained results reveal that the mass of X‚Äã(3872)ùëã3872X(3872) is considerably affected by the nuclear matter. We found a negative 25%percent2525\% shift in its mass when the saturation density was used. The shift in the current-meson coupling is also negative and it is roughly 10%percent1010\% of its vacuum value. We found the vector self energy of X‚Äã(3872)ùëã3872X(3872) at the saturated density to be Œ£œÖ=1.31subscriptŒ£ùúê1.31\Sigma_{\upsilon}=1.31 GeV. The order of shifts in the mass and residue of this particle is comparable with these of the nucleon investigated in Ref. Azizi:2014yea .

We also investigated the dependence of the ratios mX‚àó/mXsuperscriptsubscriptùëöùëãsubscriptùëöùëãm_{X}^{*}/m_{X}, Œ£œÖ/mXsubscriptŒ£ùúêsubscriptùëöùëã\Sigma_{\upsilon}/m_{X} and fX‚àó/fXsuperscriptsubscriptùëìùëãsubscriptùëìùëãf_{X}^{*}/f_{X} on the nuclear matter density. We observed that, although the dependencies are linear the results strongly depend on the nuclear matter density.

The results obtained in the present work may be used in analyses of the heavy ion collision experiments as well as those which are aiming to investigate the properties of the standard and non-conventional hadrons in nuclear medium such as PANDA Collaboration at FAIR.

Any experimental results on the in-medium properties of X‚Äã(3872)ùëã3872X(3872) and comparison of those with the results of the present study can increase our knowledge of the exotic states and help us gain useful information on the not well-known structures of the exotic states, specially the newly discovered tetraquarks.
